==Arabic alphabet==

===Letter===
'''{{ARchar|Ш§ / вҖҚШ§}}''' (вҖҷГЎlif)

# Although usually considered to be the first letter of the [[Arabic]] alphabet, the small [[hamza]] ({{ARchar|[[ШЎ]]}}) that sits on top of {{ARchar|[[ШЈ]]}} is really the first letter of the Arabic alphabet, and the tall column is its bearer. This article only deals with the lower part, the bearer, which is called {{ARchar|[[Ш§Щ„ЩҒ]]}} (вҖҷГЎlif) and, without the hamza, is used to lengthen a preceding vowel, often [[a]]. It is followed by {{ARchar|[[ШЁ]]}}.

===Pronunciation===
'''Combined with [[fathah]]:'''
<font size="5">п№¶Ш§</font> вҖ” '''ДҒ'''.


'''Combined with [[kasra]]:'''
<font size="5">п№әШ§</font> вҖ” '''Д«'''.


'''Combined with [[damma]]:'''
<font size="5">{{ARchar|п№ё}}Ш§</font> вҖ” '''Е«'''.

